results.description:
Chapter 4 in this behavior series
Photo 1:  Walking Across The Neighbor's  Lawn
The vulture walked half way across my neighbor's yard before turning to see what I was doing.  I had walked to the middle of the street to look at the squirrel.  I am amazed at how huge that wing feather is.  
Photo 2:  Coming Back Towards Me
When I backed away from the dead squirrel and back up on my lawn, the vulture turned around and walked over towards the street again.  Still keeping an eye on me.  
Photo 3:  Turkey Vulture & Bold Squirrel
All of a sudden the vulture froze & looked at something to my left.  I pulled my zoom back & discovered a squirrel was heading straight towards the vulture.  The vulture's attention was focused on this new threat now.  
Photo 4:  Squirrel Advances On The Vulture
The squirrel continued to advance on the vulture and it was chattering in an aggressive manner.  The vulture was still frozen as the squirrel got closer. Turkey vultures don't hunt or eat live prey.  
Photo 5:  Squirrel Is Too Close For The Vulture's Comfort Level
This is as close as the squirrel got before the vulture could not take it anymore and flew to the roof of the house across the street from me.  When that happened, the squirrel ran back across the street to my yard and up my pecan tree.  
Chapter 1 can be seen here:  https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/9068504
Chapter 2 can be seen here:  https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/9081559
Chapter 3 can be seen here:  https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/9092844
